  "body": "# Bug Report\n\n## Problem\n\nDuring the \"Recover with Keycard\" process you are prompted to pair the card and then enter the PIN. If you cancel after pairing but before completing the procedure, the pairing is not saved in Status and when you try again you will need to pair again. The problem is that on card the pairing slot is taken anyway and you have no way to recover it.\n\n#### Expected behavior\n\nAs soon as a pairing is done, it is saved to storage. When resuming the account recovery the pairing step is skipped if the pairing already exists.\n\n#### Actual behavior\n\nThe pairing is discarded and the pairing slot on card is wasted\n\n### Reproduction\n\n- Open Status\n- Choose account recovery with Keycard\n- Pair the card\n- Cancel in any way you want\n- Repeat step 2. You will prompted to pair the card again. The available pairing slots count is decreased",
